  <section class="section"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Forno Bravo — Carmel Valley California independent since 2003</h2>
    <p>Forno Bravo is headquartered and manufactured in Carmel Valley, California — Monterey County, Central California coast. The company has operated continuously since 2003 under independent family ownership. Forno Bravo specializes in Italian-style wood-fired pizza ovens, drawing on traditional Italian brick-oven design (barrel vault, Pompeii style, Toscana style refractory brick construction patterns) executed with California manufacturing. Independent of the major commercial foodservice consolidators (Ali Group, Middleby, ITW, Welbilt).</p>
    <p>Forno Bravo completes the California local-manufacturer corridor content that started with cluster 08 Commercial Stove/Range. The California-manufactured commercial cooking brands we cover: Imperial Range + Imperial Commercial Cooking Equipment (Corona CA, 60 miles from LA, ranges plus cluster-07 ovens), American Range Corporation (Cypress CA, 30-40 miles from LA in Orange County, ranges plus residential Performer line), Montague Company (Hayward CA, 360 miles but California-based, Ali Group ranges plus cluster-07 ovens), and Forno Bravo (Carmel Valley CA, 300 miles but California-based, Italian-style wood-fired pizza ovens). Four California-manufactured brands, four distinct product specialties, one shared California positioning.</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap">
    <h2>Forno Bravo commercial pizza ovens we service</h2>
    <div class="model-grid">
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Modena 120 / 140 / 160 — commercial mid-volume</h3><p>Commercial-scale wood-fired pizza ovens across three size configurations. Modena 120 smaller throughput; Modena 140 mid-size (most common commercial installation); Modena 160 larger throughput for higher-volume operations. Traditional Italian brick-oven construction (Pompeii or Toscana patterns) executed at Forno Bravo Carmel Valley facility.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Napolino — smaller commercial</h3><p>Space-constrained commercial configuration for restaurants wanting Italian-style wood-fired cooking without full Modena footprint. Common at smaller LA Italian-concept restaurants and operations where kitchen dimensions limit full-size pizza oven installation.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Professionale — flagship artisan</h3><p>Forno Bravo's highest-spec commercial pizza oven line. Heavier construction, premium refractory, upscale appointments for high-end restaurant installations. Common at LA fine-dining Italian restaurants where both cooking performance and visual presentation matter.</p></div>
      <div class="model-card"><h3>Vesuvio — high-capacity commercial</h3><p>High-throughput commercial configuration for operations requiring pizza-oven capacity beyond Modena 160 scale. Larger chamber, higher production throughput, typically installed at high-volume Italian restaurant operations and catering-focused commercial kitchens.</p></div>
