      <li><b>Additional smaller Italian-concept operations</b> — dozens of LA Italian restaurants running Forno Bravo Modena or Napolino as primary pizza oven where Italian heritage design matters to operator identity</li>
    </ul>
    <p>Operators choose Forno Bravo over direct Italian imports (Moretti Forni Milan, Valoriani Florence, Pavesi) typically for parts-chain accessibility reasons — California manufacturing plus California dealer network deliver faster parts and service than direct Italian imports where parts route through European supply chains with 10–14 day lead times. Forno Bravo parts reach LA in 3–7 business days typically (California state origin but Carmel Valley NorCal location adds some lead time compared to SoCal-adjacent manufacturers).</p>
  </div></section>

  <section class="section alt"><div class="wrap narrow">
    <h2>Italian brick-oven construction — Forno Bravo service specialties</h2>
    <p>Forno Bravo uses traditional Italian brick-oven construction patterns — refractory brick assembled in specific geometric arrangements (barrel vault, Pompeii style with spherical dome, Toscana style with lower dome profile) that influence heat radiation characteristics and cooking patterns. Service on Forno Bravo ovens includes several specialties distinct from Wood Stone castable-ceramic construction:</p>
    <ul class="check-list">
      <li><b>Brick pointing and mortar maintenance</b> — traditional brick construction requires periodic mortar maintenance between refractory bricks. Over 5-10 year operational lifespans, mortar gradually wears; brick pointing service restores heat-containment and cooking consistency.</li>
      <li><b>Refractory brick section replacement</b> — individual damaged or worn bricks can be replaced without full refractory teardown. Requires matching brick specification to original Forno Bravo install.</li>
      <li><b>Major refractory refurbish</b> — at 10-15 year marks or after operational damage, major refractory refurbish replaces sections of oven floor or dome. More complex than Wood Stone castable refurbish due to brick-by-brick reassembly requirements.</li>
      <li><b>Traditional Italian draft calibration</b> — Italian brick-oven design relies on specific chimney draft characteristics for proper combustion and smoke management. Service includes draft verification and chimney configuration adjustment if operational changes affect draft.</li>
      <li><b>Hybrid gas-boost service (rare models)</b> — Forno Bravo offers limited hybrid configurations combining traditional wood-fired primary with gas-boost secondary. Service covers gas valve, burner ignitor, regulator calibration, and thermocouple in addition to wood-fired brick-oven maintenance.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>LADBS chimney/venting compliance applies to Forno Bravo the same as Wood Stone and all wood-fired commercial cooking equipment. Our service includes chimney inspection and compliance coordination.</p>
  </div></section>

